          "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/nsCSPParser.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/nsCSPParser.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/nsCSPContext.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/nsCSPContext.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/nsCSPUtils.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/nsCSPUtils.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/interfaces/security/nsIContentSecurityPolicy.idl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/CSPEvalChecker.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/CSPEvalChecker.h\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/nsCSPParser.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"nsCSPParser\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/nsCSPContext.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"nsCSPContext\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/nsCSPUtils.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"CSP_LogLocalizedStr\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/interfaces/security/nsIContentSecurityPolicy.idl\",\n      \"symbol\": \"nsIContentSecurityPolicy\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/CSPEvalChecker.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"CSPEvalChecker\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/nsCSPParser.cpp\",\n      \"symbol\": \"parseContentSecurityPolicy\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/nsCSPContext.cpp\",\n      \"symbol\": \"GetAllowsInline\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/nsCSPContext.cpp\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ReportInlineViolation\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/security/nsCSPContext.cpp\",\n      \"symbol\": \"AsyncReportViolation\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The Firefox Content Security Policy enforcement infrastructure is located in dom/security/ and dom/interfaces/security/. The key components are: (1) nsCSPParser (dom/security/nsCSPParser.cpp/h) - implements the CSP directive parser using a finite state machine approach that tokenizes and validates CSP policy strings according to the W3C CSP specification. The main entry point is parseContentSecurityPolicy() which separates the input into tokens and orchestrates parsing of directives and source lists. (2) nsCSPContext (dom/security/nsCSPContext.cpp/h) - implements the primary CSP context class that holds parsed policies and provides the main enforcement interface. It implements nsIContentSecurityPolicy XPCOM interface and manages multiple CSP policies per document. Key methods for inline script evaluation include GetAllowsInline() which checks if inline scripts are permitted under the policy, and ReportInlineViolation() which handles inline script violation reporting. The class also implements AsyncReportViolation() for asynchronous violation reporting to observers. (3) nsCSPUtils (dom/security/nsCSPUtils.cpp/h) - provides utility functions for CSP operations including violation reporting helpers like CSP_LogLocalizedStr(), CSP_GetLocalizedStr(), CSP_LogMessage(), and CSP_LogStrMessage(). These functions handle console logging of CSP violations. (4) nsIContentSecurityPolicy.idl (dom/interfaces/security/) - declares the XPCOM interface definition that exposes CSP functionality to the broader Firefox codebase, including directive enums and violation type constants. (5) CSPEvalChecker (dom/security/CSPEvalChecker.cpp/h) - implements static methods CheckForWindow() and CheckForWorker() that specifically handle eval() permission checking for script-src directive. The inline script enforcement chain flows from nsCSPParser parsing policies \u2192 nsCSPContext evaluating directives against requests \u2192 ReportInlineViolation() reporting violations asynchronously through AsyncReportViolation().\"\n}\n",
